('c6aabd85-ff11-4c9e-a5a4-ef8c687f35a4','Sö 325','L 965|B 709',59.36,16.9092,': kaubi · resti : stin : eftiʀ :· su(i)ni : faþur : sin :','"Kaupi ræisti stæin æftiʀ "Svæini, faður sinn.','Köpe reste stenen efter Svene, sin fader.','Kaupi raised the stone in memory of Sveinir, his father.',NULL,NULL,'Runsten','Granit','Södermanland'),
('f7300721-2087-4fb0-a75e-e4aa3fd4afea','G 217',NULL,57.5474,18.3922,'§A nikulas : skraif : mik : in : s[--]rin e-[-]-b--r [--]rgretu ¶ mariu:messu:dah : … s : uar : brim : o^k [:] … …-r : sunnudah §B rannal(t) : berno','§A "Nikulás skrifaði mik en … … "[Ma]rgrétu "Maríumessudag … s var prím ok … [va]r sunnudagr. §B "Ragnvaldr. "Berno.','§A Nikulas skrev (ristade) mig … Margareta på Mariemässodagen, [då] <s> var prim(runa) och … söndag(sruna). §B Ragnvald. Berno.','§A Nikulás wrote me but … Margréta day of Mary''s-mass. Then S was the prime-stave and … was the Sunday[-stave]. §B Ragnvaldr. Berno.','1400-talet (A)',NULL,'Putsinskrifter','Kalkputs','Gotland'),
('dbd21156-8e9b-4935-8bc0-0706ccd1c1e3','G 328',NULL,57.8537,19.0236,'[…m] : lit- : gera : -ta[-- : --- : -…]','"… lét[u](?) gera [s]te[in] … …','… lät(?) göra stenen…','… had(?) the stone made …',NULL,NULL,'Fragment av gravsten','Sten','Gotland'),
('c3066ebd-10ab-4651-978a-6d80bc4e114c','G 306','L 1701',57.8393,18.6885,'[× gan]uiþr : o^k · botuiþr · [kaslla · o^k · þair] letu · haga · an stain · o^k · yfr · sin faþur · butair · aitin · guþ · alssualtuhr · hafi · þina · sial · o^k þa uar · l · o… pirimst^efr o^k fir sunutahr · o^k en ha do','"Gagnviðr ok "Botviðr [i] "Kassla/"Kassle ok þæiʀ let haggva æin stæin ok yfiʀ sinn faður, "Botgæiʀ hæitin. "Guð allsvaldugʀ hafi þina sial. Ok þa vaʀ l o[k](?) primstafʀ ok fir sunnudagʀ ok en hann do.','Ganvid och Botvid (i) Kassla och de lät hugga en sten och över sin fader, ''salig'' Botair. Den allsmäktige Gud må hava din själ. Och då var <l> och(?)… primstav och fir söndags(runa) och när han dog.','Gagnviðr and Bótviðr in Kassla/Kassle, and they had a stone cut over their father, he was called Bótgeirr. May all-powerful God have (= take) their souls. And then L and(?) (was) the prime-stave and Fir (= F-rune?) the Sunday(-stave) when he died.','1419',NULL,'Gravhäll','Kalksten','Gotland'),
('ea23927a-073d-4591-976c-306d715c6e67','Sö 295',NULL,59.1663,17.7425,'[han ua iguars| |sun]','Hann vaʀ "Ingvars sunʀ.','Han var(?) Ingvars son.','He was Ingvarr''s son.',NULL,'Enligt Lerche Nielsen 2010:230 har inskriften ej återfunnits i Peringskiölds anteckningar F h 31. Jämför Dybecks Svenska Run-urkunder 2, 1857, s. 409. Inskriften får tills vidare anses för osäker.','Runsten','Sten','Södermanland'),
('cf576fec-c918-4cb2-99b6-6c93b688375a','G 63','L 1777',57.221,18.2367,': fa^rgair : lit : mik : [(g)]iea^ra : (y)fer : s[in : fa^þ]ur : u[k] : moþ[o]r [:] b[ot]frir : [ok] : [ruþui : ok : auþuatr] : ok : mik :[+] (k)[rist]r : ma[i]u : sun na^þi : a^lum : sum : hiea^r : huila^s : uair : uk aʟum : krisnum : si(a)[l+]um','"Fargeirr lét mik gera yfir sinn fǫður ok móður "Bótfreðr ok "Hróðvé, ok "Auðhvatr/"Auðvaldr hjó mik. "Kristr, "Maríu sonr, náði ǫllum sem hér hvílask undir, ok ǫllum kristnum sálum.','Fargair lät göra mig över sin fader och moder Botfrid och Rudvi, och Audvat (el. Audvald) högg(?) mig. Krist, Marias son, vare nådig mot alla, som här under vilar, och mot alla kristna själar.','Fargeirr had me made over his father and mother Bótfreðr and Hróðvé, and Auðhvatr/Auðvaldr cut me. Christ, son of Mary, be gracious to all who rest hereunder, and to all Christian souls.','1300-talet',NULL,'Gravhäll','Ljusgrå kalksten','Gotland'),
('03b14056-0439-4f45-b110-e7b4f5c07a1d','G 361',NULL,56.9374,18.1545,'§A þu(n)u(r)þurus §B ---hotrn--','§A … §B …','…','§A … §B …','675–775/800 (Imer 2007)',NULL,'Bleck','Koppar','Gotland'),
('68a148af-1ea1-4046-935c-400799307155','Sm 64','L 1246|B 1033',57.21,14.0395,'þurun : sati : stin : eftiʀ : oskil : buta : sin : auk : eftiʀ · sunu : sina : suin : auk : tufa : kuþ : hialbi : selu : þiʀa','"Þorunnr satti stæin æftiʀ "Askel, bonda sinn, ok æftiʀ sunu sina "Svæin ok "Tofa. "Guð hialpi salu þæiʀa.','Torunn satte stenen efter Eskil, sin make, och efter sina söner Sven och Tove. Gud hjälpe deras själ.','Þórunnr placed the stone in memory of Áskell, her husbandman and in memory of her sons Sveinn and Tófi. May God help their souls.',NULL,NULL,'Runsten','Amfibolit','Småland'),
