('bcb110fb-5db8-442a-b2de-b871fc164bf0','G 201','L 1741',57.4799,18.3908,'ha^lt[ia]uþ · a^uþualtz : [enkia : -]tliks : han lit : hualf : otki[era] · yfir : sin : sun : boztan · ok han : baþ : [l]a- : biþia : fyr[ir] ha^ns ·: sial · iakau[b]r : gierþi : stain : r^oþmas:a^rfi','"Hallþjóð, "Auðvalds ekkja "[A]tlings, hon lét hvalf atgera yfir sinn son "Bótstein, ok hon bað: Lá[t] biðja fyrir hans sál! "Jakobr gerði stein, "Hróðmarsarfi/"Rodmarsarve.','Halldjaud, änka efter Audvald (i) Atlings, hon lät göra gravvården över sin son Botstain, och hon bad: Låt bedja för hans själ! Jakob (i) Rodmarsarve(?) gjorde stenen.','Hallþjóð, widow of Auðvaldr of Atling, she had the vault made over her son Bótsteinn, and she ordered: Pray for his soul! Jakobr of Hróðmarsarfi/Rodmarsarve made the stone.','1300-talet',NULL,'Gravhäll','Kalksten','Gotland'),
('7856a719-affe-431c-b7b4-f4308d6722ef','Sö 108','L 969|B 751',59.375,16.5457,'kunulfʀ : raisti : stein : þansi : at : ulf : faþur : sin : han : uaʀ i : faru : miþ : ikuari :','"Gunnulfʀ ræisti stæin þannsi at "Ulf, faður sinn. Hann vaʀ i faru með "Ingvari.','Gunnulv reste denna sten efter Ulv, sin fader. Han var på färd med Ingvar.','Gunnulfr raised this stone in memory of Ulfr, his father. He was on a voyage with Ingvarr.',NULL,NULL,'Runsten','Granit','Södermanland'),
