('d8b1d1de-409c-4b65-9e17-b4229fd02cd6','Sö 137','L 868|B 807',58.9254,17.0986,'§A þura : raisþi : stin : þ--si at : ubi : buanti : sin §B : stain : saʀ:si : stanr : at : ybi : o þik·staþi : at ¶ : þuru : uar : han : uestarla : uakti : karla ¶ [sa þar] · sunr þaþ · traknasuatau(k)i(f)maʀ[sua]','§A "Þóra reisti stein þ[enn]a at "Œpi, bónda sinn. §B Steinn þessi stendr at "Œpi á þingstaði at "Þóru ver. Hann vestarla væknti(?) karla, sá þar sonr þat …','§A Tora reste denna sten efter Öpir, sin make. §B Denna sten står efter Öpir på tingstaden efter Toras man. Han västerut väpnade(?) (sitt) husfolk(?) …','§A Þóra raised this stone in memory of Œpir, her husbandman. §B This stone stands in memory of Œpir, on the Assembly-place in memory of Þóra''s husband. He armed(?) (his) men in the west. The son saw this there …',NULL,'Ristad i raka rader, sista raden med stavlösa runor förutom sista ordet.','Runsten','Gråsten','Södermanland'),
