('df790209-96b5-40aa-a078-883c16c7f0cd','Sö 55',NULL,58.9598,16.6163,'þorstain (l)(i)… …sa : stain : þena : … sik : sialfan : auk : sun : sin : hefni : uaʀ til : enklans : ukr : trenkr : farin : uarþ : þa · haima : at : harmi tauþr kuþ hialbi : sialu : þaima bruni : auk : sloþi : þaiʀ …(u) stan þena','"Þorstæinn le[t ræi]sa stæin þenna [æftiʀ] sik sialfan ok sun sinn "Hæfni. Vaʀ til "Ænglands ungʀ drængʀ farinn, varð þa hæima at harmi dauðr. "Guð hialpi sialu þæiʀa. "Bruni ok "Sloði þæiʀ [rist]u stæin þenna.','Torsten lät resa denna sten [efter] sig själv och sin son Hävne. Till England var den unge mannen faren, blev sedan hemma till sorg död. Gud hjälpe deras själ. Brune och Slode de ristade denna sten.','Þorsteinn had this stone raised in memory of himself and his son Hefnir. The young valiant man travelled to England; then died grievously at home. May God help their souls. Brúni and Slóði, they carved this stone.',NULL,'Hopfogades och restes 1936.','Runsten','Granit','Södermanland'),
('0c85b1af-ffdf-47d9-bed2-2c9cc8cea6af','Sm 54',NULL,56.955,13.5311,'guþ gøme · h : igibrʀhtso(n) ¶ sial : a^n : knutær ¶ hiar likær','"Guð gøymi H[erra] "Engibriktssunaʀ sial. Hann "Knutr hiar liggʀ.','Gud bevare herr Ingebrekts sons själ. Han Knut ligger här.','God may protect Herra Engibriktsson''s soul. He Knútr lies here.','1200-talet','Enkel ornamentik, ramlinjer och enkla kors','Gravhäll','Sten','Småland'),
('ddd5f534-aaff-4eb9-ad63-7b1e82309a26','Sö Fv1948;289',NULL,58.9267,17.0993,'ostriþ : lit : -ira : ku(m)… …usi ⁓ at : anunt ⁓ auk : raknualt : sun : sin ⁓: urþu : ta…ʀ : - (t)an…-…(k)u : ua-u : rikiʀ : o rauniki : ak : snialastiʀ : i : suiþiuþu','"Astrið let [g]æra kum[bl þa]usi at "Anund ok "Ragnvald, sun sinn. Urðu da[uði]ʀ [i] "Dan[mar]ku, va[ʀ]u rikiʀ a "Rauningi ok sniallastiʀ i "Sveþiuðu.','Astrid lät göra detta minnesmärke efter Anund och Ragnvald, sin son. De dog i Danmark. De var mäktiga i Röninge och raskast i Svitjod.','Ástríðr had these monuments made in memory of Ǫnundr and Ragnvaldr, her son. (They) died in Denmark, were powerful in Rauningi and the ablest in Sweden.',NULL,'Funnen vid omläggning av Aspa bro 1937.','Runsten','Granit','Södermanland'),
